My response to California Bipolar Winter ☀️ 🥶🤣

In 2022 I witnessed the sovereignty of God; I saw His hand of compassion, kindness and experienced His arms of comfort and care. It was the first year without my mother. Her absence wounded me deeply and I didn’t know how I would make it. There were days when I couldn’t get out of bed but God was near. There were dark nights and lonely days but also moments of pure joy and laughter. It was the first year of many things: decisions, dreams and the culmination of several chapters.. Thank you to those who stood beside me and lifted my arms when I couldn’t. Thank you to those who extended me grace and patience…I saw God through you. God was faithful; He kept me. My mother is now dancing in the streets of gold and I AM STILL STANDING. • Thank you 2022 for all you taught me.

Una de las mayores bendiciones de mi vida ha sido contar con amigos que me impulsan a ser una mejor persona y reflejar verdaderamente a Jesús en mi vida. @jdavidaguilar ha sido uno de esos amigos y juntos hemos tenido conversaciones honestas que a veces pueden resultar un poco incómodas, pero que siempre nos llevan al fondo de la situación. Me gustaría invitarte a escuchar uno de estos intercambios en este podcast. Espero que este episodio te brinde una perspectiva diferente sobre tu situación y que puedas encontrar a Dios incluso en medio del dolor, la injusticia y/o la incertidumbre que puedas estar enfrentando. • @conversacioneslid •

Art is all around us, from the rhythm of music to the flavor of food. For me, every moment is an opportunity to capture a glimpse of God's masterpiece. For over a decade, I've been serving as a creative director and stylist, but recently I found the courage to step behind the camera myself. There's nothing quite like the power of photography to freeze a moment in time and bring it to life. I'm loving this new creative outlet and can't wait to see where it takes me. -Poncho • @hezandco • #leica #leicaphotography #leicam

I remember this Sunday at Woodlawn Church, I was in the green room praying and asking God to use me. I felt honored to be there but so inadequate. As my walk with the Lord has deepened through various experiences, circumstances, and situations, I've learned that I have nothing to prove and nothing to strive for. God thinks I'm "good," and He always shows up and does what He does best. It's never been about my capability but about His kindness and grace. He will always show up!
El siempre tiene cuidado de mi.

Sunday, April 23, 2023 marked the end of my journey as worship pastor at @faithchapelsd in Spring Valley, CA. It was a significant chapter in my life, filled with both joy and hardship. I was hired during the same month my mother was diagnosed with stage 4 cancer. In the midst of this difficult season, the church opened their doors and provided unwavering support for my family and me.

Week after week, I stood on that stage, striving to lead others while navigating my own doubts, pain, and uncertainty. I wasn’t a perfect leader, but I poured my heart into loving and shepherding a team that deserved all the care and compassion. They uplifted me, just as I did for them. When the time came to bid farewell to my mother, the church embraced me, shared in my sorrow, and showered me with love. I will forever be indebted to their kindness.

Even as I embarked on journeys across the country and abroad, my team remained steadfast, holding down the fort and cheering me on. Their unwavering support was a priceless gift. Now, as I take a step of faith and pursue my own dreams, they continue to stand by me. Serving this community has been a divine gift, and I consider myself a son of this house. I pray that I make them proud. I eagerly anticipate the future and all that it holds.
